{"tid":2113204,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"［學野］白宮發言人Kayleigh McEnany 筆記曝光 WSJ驚嘆：So Organized!","createTime":"2020-07-18T03:19:34.000Z","updateTime":"2020-07-18T10:42:25.000Z","uid":48083,"like":88,"dislike":4,"uniUserReply":48,"replies":[{"pid":"664e12531340ec49a66051b7781c6cd69fac1a0d","tid":2113204,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:19:34.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/ynerjNh.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FynerjNh.jpg&h=20b6293b&s={SIZE}\" /><img src=\"https://na.cx/i/ZjJvMsi.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FZjJvMsi.jpg&h=35231617&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nThanks to the photo, we know what McEnany has brought to the task of covering for<del> a<del> lazy</del>, mendacious, racist, sexist, misanthropic</del> president: first-rate organizational skills.<br />\n<br />\nDon&rsquo;t underestimate their importance. At any given briefing, McEnany turns frequently to her impeccably tabulated topic binder. It&rsquo;s not difficult, after all, to anticipate what issues will be of interest to White House reporters. Every day McEnany and her colleagues in the White House communications shop receive emails from correspondents asking about this matter or that matter. The assembled files enable McEnany to pepper her responses with specifics &mdash; quotes, statistics, anecdotes, whatever advances her cause....<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;[M]ost press secretaries routinely come to the podium armed with talking points, opening statements and comebacks for likely questions given the topics of the moment,&rdquo; emails Tom DeFrank, a contributing editor to National Journal who has covered 10 presidents. &ldquo;But Kayleigh arrives with the War and Peace of briefing materials. In more than 52 years of covering WH briefings &hellip; I&rsquo;ve never seen a binder that prodigious at a regular briefing.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/07/17/kayleigh-mcenany-watch-so-organized/%3foutputType=amp\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.hk%2Famp%2Fs%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2020%2F07%2F17%2Fkayleigh-mcenany-watch-so-organized%2F%253foutputType%3Damp&d=G%2B3HFD3c3HuaSfC8k9KTiXKg77Sy3LnB9Oyli8DN%2Bms%3D&h=8ae3cc50\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/07/17/kayleigh-mcenany-watch-so-organized/%3foutputType=amp</a>"},{"pid":"09651a1b56730d726bf74b784032a90708810b29","tid":2113204,"uid":48083,"like":42,"dislike":0,"score":42,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:21:43.000Z","msg":"McEnany&rsquo;s briefing materials have played a starring role in her trademark mic-drop closing remarks. On May 6, for example, she read from her prepared work as she blasted the media for alleged failures:<br />\n<br />\nDoes Vox want to take back that they proclaim that the coronavirus would not be a deadly pandemic? <br />\n<strong><span class=\"red\"><br />\nDoes The Washington Post want to take back that they told Americans to get a grip, the flu is bigger than the coronavirus? <br />\n<br />\nDoes The Washington Post, likewise, want to take back that our brains are causing us to exaggerate the threat of the coronavirus? </span></strong><br />\n<br />\nDoes the New York Times want to take back that fear of the virus may be spreading faster than the virus itself? <br />\n<br />\nDoes NPR want to take back that the flu was a much bigger threat than the coronavirus? <br />\n<strong><span class=\"green\"><span class=\"red\"><br />\nAnd finally, once again The Washington Post: Would they like to take back that the government should not respond aggressively to the coronavirus? </span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nI&rsquo;ll leave you with those questions, and maybe you&rsquo;ll have some answers in a few days.<br />\n<br />\nWashington post 又有器度登番哩段野出嚟<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"666bcc2ae24710b417ce5c110462e046173b4930","tid":2113204,"uid":52215,"like":8,"dislike":24,"score":-16,"citedBy":5,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:22:40.000Z","msg":"人地幫佢執唔得？"},{"pid":"afd81e9974681b9d749ac1d7498c582c3de6f496","tid":2113204,"uid":51271,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:23:00.000Z","msg":"睇唔到有無HK"},{"pid":"fc5b804c1193e42040431c74de5d8069406b33cb","tid":2113204,"uid":261913,"like":13,"dislike":2,"score":11,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:23:47.000Z","msg":"識玩緊係J佢個樣<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8c6918ee27dad5377634ae778c15108721cb6721","tid":2113204,"uid":171849,"like":25,"dislike":0,"score":25,"citedBy":5,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:24:11.000Z","msg":"<blockquote> a lazy, mendacious, racist, sexist, misanthropic president:</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nWSJ點解可以咁唔中立<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9dcdaf29fbb3a11513d166889fc8ddb029cbc96d","tid":2113204,"uid":48083,"like":28,"dislike":0,"score":28,"quote":{"pid":"666bcc2ae24710b417ce5c110462e046173b4930","tid":2113204,"uid":52215,"like":8,"dislike":24,"score":-16,"citedBy":5,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:22:40.000Z","msg":"人地幫佢執唔得？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:24:27.000Z","msg":"有人同佢一齊做<br />\n但淨係要讀熟哂咁多題目都大撚鑊<br />\n啲資料係不斷更新<br />\n<br />\nEvery day McEnany and her colleagues in the White House communications shop receive emails from correspondents asking about this matter or that matter. The assembled files enable McEnany to pepper her responses with specifics &mdash; quotes, statistics, anecdotes, whatever advances her cause...."},{"pid":"afe8a36d0efb1daecdde97a0039a6e8ea0e5a97b","tid":2113204,"uid":270220,"like":46,"dislike":0,"score":46,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-18T03:24